(2338, 181, 'it is an educational game app with creative activities and puzzles , the age group will be 2-8 years old , include all these features mini-games, animated stories, drawing tools, quizzes, video playback, parental control features, the app will be only iOS platform', 'Thank you for providing these details about your educational game app for kids! It sounds like a fun and engaging project.\n\nTo ensure we fully understand your vision for the app, I have a few clarifying questions:\n\n1.  **Educational Content & Games:** Could you elaborate on the specific learning objectives or subjects you want to focus on within the app (e.g., early literacy, basic math, cognitive skills, creativity)? Also, what types of mini-games are you envisioning (e.g., matching games, puzzle-solving, simple coding challenges) and approximately how many unique games would you like to include initially?\n2.  **Content Management & Interactivity:** For the animated stories and video playback, will these be pre-recorded videos, or do you expect interactive elements within the stories? How will new stories, drawing tools, or quiz content be managed and updated after the app is launched? Will there be a need for an admin panel or Content Management System (CMS)?\n3.  **Parental Controls & Monetization:** Regarding parental control features, what specific functionalities are essential (e.g., screen time limits, progress tracking for children, restricting access to certain content, managing in-app purchases)? Also, do you have a monetization strategy in mind for the app (e.g., one-time purchase, subscription model for premium content, free with ads)?\n\nDo you have any more requirements to add, or are you ready to complete the requirements? Please write \'complete requirement\' if you\'re done.', '2025-11-17 05:32:19'),
(2339, 181, 'the subject will be maths and english ,the mini-games will be matching games, puzzle-solving, and approx 5 unique game should be there , yes they will be pre-recorded videos , yes it will have the admin panel, yes there should be screen time limit and also progress tracking children', NULL, '2025-11-17 05:34:57'),
(2340, 181, 'the subject will be maths and english ,the mini-games will be matching games, puzzle-solving, and approx 5 unique game should be there , yes they will be pre-recorded videos , yes it will have the admin panel, yes there should be screen time limit and also progress tracking children', 'Thank you for providing more details! This helps us understand the scope better.\n\nLet\'s clarify these new requirements:\n\n1.  **Subject Matter (Maths and English for 2-8 years old):**\n    *   Could you specify the key learning areas or topics within Maths (e.g., basic counting, number recognition, simple addition/subtraction) and English (e.g., alphabet recognition, phonics, sight words, basic vocabulary) that you want to prioritize for this age group?\n    *   Are there any specific educational standards or curriculum guidelines you\'d like the content to align with?\n\n2.  **Mini-games (Matching games, puzzle-solving, approx 5 unique games):**\n    *   For the matching games, do you envision picture-to-picture matching, word-to-picture matching, number matching, or something else? Can you give an example?\n    *   For the puzzle-solving games, what type of puzzles are you thinking of (e.g., jigsaw puzzles, shape puzzles, simple logic puzzles)?\n    *   Regarding the \"approx 5 unique games,\" do you have any initial ideas for the other 3 game types beyond matching and puzzle-solving, or would you like us to suggest some creative activities suitable for the age group and subjects?\n\n3.  **Pre-recorded Videos:**\n    *   What kind of content will these pre-recorded videos feature? Will they be animated lessons, storytelling, songs, or real-world examples?\n    *   Will these videos be integrated into specific learning activities, or will they be available as standalone content for children to watch?\n\n4.  **Admin Panel:**\n    *   What specific functionalities do you expect the admin panel to have? For example, will it be used to manage game content, add/edit video