(2384, 144, 'the app is gym fitness tracing app ..the age range is 18-30 years old', 'That\'s a great start! A gym fitness tracking app for the 18-30 age range sounds like an engaging project.\n\nTo ensure we capture all the details for your gym fitness tracking app:\n1.  What specific fitness metrics or activities should the app track? For example, should it track workouts, calories burned, steps, heart rate, or offer personalized workout plans?\n2.  How should the app handle user data and privacy, especially considering the age range? Will users create profiles, store their fitness history, and will there be any social sharing or community features?\n\nDo you have any more requirements to add, or are you ready to complete the requirements? Please write \'complete requirement\' if you\'re done.', '2025-11-17 10:14:50'),
(2385, 144, 'its an workout tracking app and yes user will be going to create the profiles for storing their fitness history and also having the feature of social sharing', NULL, '2025-11-17 10:16:02'),
(2386, 144, 'its an workout tracking app and yes user will be going to create the profiles for storing their fitness history and also having the feature of social sharing', 'Regarding the workout tracking and fitness history, what specific metrics or data points do you envision users tracking (e.g., reps, sets, weight lifted, distance, duration, calories burned)? Also, how should users be able to view or analyze their fitness history (e.g., daily logs, weekly summaries, progress charts over time)?\n\nFor the user profiles and social sharing feature, what kind of social interactions are you looking for (e.g., sharing workout achievements, challenging friends, commenting on posts)? And what specific information will be part of the user profile beyond basic fitness history (e.g., profile picture, bio, fitness goals)?\n\nDo you have any more requirements to add, or are you ready to complete the requirements? Please write \'complete requirement\' if you\'re done.', '2025-11-17 10:16:27'),
(2387, 144, 'add these specific parameters reps, sets, weight lifted, distance, duration,......useer view their fitness history through weekly summaries ......for social sharing it need commenting on post and also sharing wokrout achievemnets', NULL, '2025-11-17 10:18:03'),
(2388, 144, 'add these specific parameters reps, sets, weight lifted, distance, duration,......useer view their fitness history through weekly summaries ......for social sharing it need commenting on post and also sharing wokrout achievemnets', 'Thank you for providing those details! It helps us understand the scope of the fitness tracking app.\n\nRegarding the specific parameters like reps, sets, weight lifted, distance, and duration:\n1.  How will users input these parameters into the app? For example, will it be manual entry, or will there be integration with wearable devices or gym equipment?\n2.  Are there any specific units of measurement required for these parameters (e.g., kilograms vs. pounds for weight, kilometers vs. miles for distance), and will there be any validation rules for the input?\n\nFor viewing fitness history through weekly summaries:\n1.  What specific metrics or data points should be highlighted or calculated in these weekly summaries? For example, total workout time, average intensity, personal bests achieved, or progress charts?\n2.  Will users need the ability to export these summaries (e.g., as a PDF or image) or share them outside the app?\n\nRegarding social sharing, including commenting on posts and sharing workout achievements:\n1.  What kind of content will users be able to comment on? Will it be limited to other users\' workout posts, or will there be a broader feed with other types of content?\n2.  How will workout achievements be defined and presented for sharing? For instance, will they be automatically generated badges, user-selected milestones, or customizable templates for sharing on external platforms?\n\nDo you have any more requirements to add, or are you ready to complete the requirements? Please write \'complete requirement\' if you\'re done.', '2025-11-17 10:18:10'),
(2389, 144, 'it will be manual entry ..yes measuring parameters in kg ...........total workout time should be highligted ...export in pdf ....limited to other users\' workout posts, user-selected milestones', NULL, '2025-11-17 10:20:18'),
(2390, 144, 'it will be manual entry ..yes measuring parameters in kg ...........total workout time should be highligted ...export in pdf ....limited to other users\' workout posts, user-selected milestones', 'Thank you for providing those details!\n\nRegarding the manual entry and measurement parameters, will users input data for each parameter (reps, sets, weight, etc.) in separate fields, or will there be a more flexible input method? Also, besides kilograms, will the app need to support other units of measurement (e.g., pounds for weight, miles/km for distance) with conversion options?\n\nAnd for the social sharing feature, when you mention \'limited to other users\' workout posts,\' does this imply a follower-based system where users only see content from people they follow, or are there other privacy controls? How should users define and track their \'user-selected milestones\' within the app (e.g., setting personal bests, achieving specific fitness goals)?\n\nDo you have any more requirements to add, or are you ready to complete the requirements? Please write \'complete requirement\' if you\'re done.', '2025-11-17 10:20:40'),
(2391, 144, 'yes input each parameters in seperate fields. yes i need follower-based system,', NULL, '2025-11-17 10:21:41'),
(2392, 144, 'yes input each parameters in seperate fields. yes i need follower-based system,', 'Thank you for clarifying that parameters should be input in separate fields and that you need a follower-based system.\n\nRegarding the separate input fields for parameters like reps, sets, and weight lifted:\n1. How should these separate fields be presented to the user within the app interface? For example, will there be distinct input boxes for each parameter (e.g., one for \'reps\', one for \'sets\', one for \'weight lifted\') on a single screen, or will they be guided through a step-by-step input process?\n2. Are there any specific validation rules for these input fields, such as requiring only numeric input, or minimum/maximum values for certain parameters (e.g., reps cannot be negative)?\n\nRegarding the follower-based system:\n1. What specific functionalities should the follower-based system include? For example, will users be able to send follow requests, accept/decline requests, see a list of their followers/following, or block users?\n2. How will the follower-based system integrate with the social sharing feature? For instance, will only followers be able to see workout achievements and comment on posts, or will there be options for public and private posts?\n\nDo you have any more requirements to add, or are you ready to complete the requirements? Please write \'complete requirement\' if you\'re done.', '2025-11-17 10:21:47'),
(2393, 144, 'it depends on you how to present the separate field ..its upon you , no specific validation rule also ,yes user will be able to do all these will users be able to send follow requests, accept/decline requests, see a list of their followers/following, or block users', NULL, '2025-11-17 10:24:09'),
